spans.text: the dewy frontlet of the day
to hail my Valentine , Sweet maiden , fairest of the virgin throng
the fragrant bosom of the spring , Sweet
the flowers be fragrant as the morn
Those flowers my woven chaplet must adorn , That ditty
while my tongue shall chant her beauty's praise
carol this sweet hour of prime , Each to his mate , a roundelay of love
of my love reveal , Full many a fond expedient have I tried My warmest wish in silence to conceal
indulged my musing mood , And there alone
I dare to plight my vow
the feast of love decreed , Emboldened
to hear how sore my heart does bleed
Nor softest melody can utter well
Nor softest melody can utter well
Those bowers where angels sweet division sing
of these thy blooming train O bid some sylph in morning dreams relate , Ere yet my love awake , my secret pain
of these thy blooming train O bid
